# solarized dark — Ethan Schoonover's canonical 16-colour ANSI mapping
# (the shipped "Solarized Dark Patched"/"Higher Contrast" builtins are forks
# with shifted bases, so we carry the original). Two deliberate deviations:
#   - 7/15 (base2/base3) are near-white in stock and make Claude Code headers
#     blaze; per this repo's convention both become body fg (base1).
#   - 8 (bright black) is base03 in stock — i.e. EXACTLY the background, so
#     dim text renders invisible. Remapped to base01.
# Body fg is base1 (5.6:1), one step up the base ladder from stock base0
# (4.8:1), matching the lift theme-sync applies in nvim.
